1
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:40,800
<i>Give me back my husband, Felma!</i>

2
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,333
<i>- You're a liar!
- Have pity on me.</i>

3
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:43,500
<i> You didn't even fight back?</i>

4
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:45,100
<i>So I would appear
to be a victim.</i>

5
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:46,500
<i>I'm the one being
oppressed, right?</i>

6
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:48,633
<i> She didn't go to school today.</i>

7
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:51,467
<i>She said she's going to spend
some special time</i>

8
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:53,433
<i> with some important people.</i>

9
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:54,833
<i>- Coleen?
- Jessica,</i>

10
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:56,500
<i> Mrs. Wilson is calling.</i>

11
00:00:56,633 --> 00:00:59,567
<i>You're here, so it only means
your father's here too!</i>

12
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:00,367
<i> Hello, Coleen?</i>

13
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,300
<i>Mom, Andrea found out the truth.</i>

14
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:03,300
<i>- Wait, sweetie. Jeffrey!
- Jeff!</i>

15
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:04,433
<i>- Jeff! Jeff!
- Jeffrey!</i>

16
00:01:04,567 --> 00:01:05,967
<i> It's easy for you to meddle.</i>

17
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,000
<i>Because you don't know
what we've been through.</i>

18
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:09,733
<i>Because we don't have a father.</i>

19
00:01:09,867 --> 00:01:12,400
<i>They're looking for a place
to move into.</i>

20
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:13,367
<i> I will face him!</i>

21
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:14,167
<i>- Jeffrey!
- Don't try to stop me.</i>

22
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:15,200
<i>- Jeffrey!
- Jeff, Felma!</i>

23
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:17,100
<i>- Get out of this house!
- Andrea, stop it!</i>

24
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:18,667
<i> Get out!</i>

25
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:21,300
<i>- Get your hands off my sister!
- Jeffrey!</i>

26
00:01:21,433 --> 00:01:22,700
<i>Mom, you have to kick them
out of this house.</i>

27
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,400
<i>I can't live in the same house
with that man!</i>

28
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:27,033
<i>- Get out of here!
- Jeff!</i>

29
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:29,933
<i>- Let me be!
- That's enough!</i>

30
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:32,300
<i> That's enough!</i>

31
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:42,033
You jerk!

32
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:45,900
I was trying for Felma
and Manuel not to cross paths,

33
00:01:46,033 --> 00:01:47,300
but you helped make it happen!

34
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:49,833
You're unbelievable. That hurts.

35
00:01:49,967 --> 00:01:51,267
Well, the person is my friend.

36
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,600
Of course, I just gave him
a job.

37
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:57,833
How was I to know that Felma
and Manuel would cross paths?

38
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,200
And if you were
in Felma's situation,

39
00:02:00,333 --> 00:02:00,967
aren't you going
to help him out?

40
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:02,700
I will help her right away.

41
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:04,600
But I will not keep it
a secret from you!

42
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:06,867
I will tell you everything!

43
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,433
Okay, Abel?

44
00:02:08,567 --> 00:02:13,200
Wait a minute, why are you
so eager to help Manuel?

45
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,633
You probably have some
kind of agreement, don't you?

46
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,333
What agreement?

47
00:02:17,467 --> 00:02:19,600
He's going to keep
all your secrets.

48
00:02:20,167 --> 00:02:22,100
That's why you keep
giving in to him.

49
00:02:22,233 --> 00:02:23,467
Admit it, Abelardo!

50
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,800
- What?
- Tell me!

51
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:26,033
You have a side chick,
don't you?

52
00:02:27,067 --> 00:02:28,767
My god, Paz!

53
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:32,400
After all these years together,
you still get jealous?

54
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:34,833
You're unbelievable.

55
00:02:35,433 --> 00:02:36,700
There's no one.
I don't have a side chick.

56
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:37,367
No one!

57
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:38,100
Tell me the truth!

58
00:02:38,233 --> 00:02:39,200
No one!

59
00:02:41,867 --> 00:02:43,200
You're good at pretending.

60
00:02:44,367 --> 00:02:45,833
You were pretending that guy
wasn't even here

61
00:02:45,967 --> 00:02:47,100
when Hazel barged in?

62
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:49,733
Mom didn't know it at that time.

63
00:02:50,933 --> 00:02:54,233
I didn't even want him
to stay here.

64
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:57,500
You're father was in a really
tight spot.

65
00:02:57,867 --> 00:02:59,733
Can you stop saying
that he's our father!

66
00:02:59,867 --> 00:03:01,000
He's long been gone!

67
00:03:01,467 --> 00:03:04,033
Can you not talk to me
like that?

68
00:03:07,533 --> 00:03:10,000
We have to calm down.

69
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:11,667
Mom, we feel betrayed.

70
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:14,433
You know what we've
been through, right?

71
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,467
How Andrea and I suffered?

72
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:19,300
Mom, we only have each other.

73
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:20,700
It's just us who've been
supporting each other.

74
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:23,533
And then what? This man suddenly
comes in?

75
00:03:23,967 --> 00:03:25,367
So now we don't matter?

76
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:29,933
That's not true, Dear.

77
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,533
I'm not ignoring
your feelings.

78
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:34,833
That's the reason why
we can't tell you.

79
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:39,067
Because we know how you'll feel.

80
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:42,667
I know that you're still mad
at your father

81
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,667
and you can't forgive him.

82
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:47,733
I will not force you to do that.

83
00:03:48,733 --> 00:03:50,900
You have to believe me.

84
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:54,467
I know where this is going.

85
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:58,567
You're going to convince us
to let that man stay here!

86
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:01,233
They'll only be here
until tomorrow.

87
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:02,533
Tomorrow?

88
00:04:03,067 --> 00:04:05,400
The next day, the day
after that, next week?

89
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:07,800
What's wrong with that?

90
00:04:08,667 --> 00:04:10,067
You're not here
during the day anyway.

91
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,533
You're always at work.

92
00:04:11,667 --> 00:04:14,867
You can come home late,
so you'll be ready to sleep.

93
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,467
That way,
you won't get to see them!

94
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:19,467
Unbelievable!

95
00:04:20,133 --> 00:04:22,000
So you have our life
planned out.

96
00:04:22,733 --> 00:04:24,167
You know what,
this is all your fault.

97
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:27,400
You wanted to have
a father so bad

98
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:30,133
that it doesn't matter
if our family falls apart.

99
00:04:30,267 --> 00:04:31,467
Please!

100
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:34,833
Can you stop fighting?

101
00:04:34,967 --> 00:04:38,600
Fine, okay, Mom,
you have a choice...

102
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:42,633
It's either you choose
Manuel and Jessica,

103
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:45,200
or my brother and I.

104
00:04:53,267 --> 00:04:54,733
Thank you, Didang.

105
00:04:55,767 --> 00:04:56,667
Here you go, Sir.

106
00:04:57,433 --> 00:04:58,300
Thank you.

107
00:05:02,667 --> 00:05:03,800
Sweetie, are you okay?

108
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,967
I'm still trying to make sense
of what happened, Dad.

109
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:08,767
I'm sorry about that.

110
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:11,267
You got dragged into my problem.

111
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:14,600
Dad, this is my problem, too.

112
00:05:15,367 --> 00:05:16,900
They're my siblings.

113
00:05:17,467 --> 00:05:19,433
I understand how they feel.

114
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,133
But I'm so sad for you.

115
00:05:22,267 --> 00:05:24,267
I know how much
this is hurting you.

116
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:25,800
You know what, Sweetie?

117
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:29,367
The most painful thing is...

118
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,367
even though they're so
angry at me,

119
00:05:35,367 --> 00:05:37,167
I still want to hold them
in my arms.

120
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,267
If only it weren't too much
to ask God

121
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,200
that your siblings and I
could be reconciled,

122
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:46,300
just as I was with Felma
and Coleen.

123
00:05:46,867 --> 00:05:48,700
I hope so, too, Dad.

124
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:52,867
We never know, Miss Felma's
talking to them right now.

125
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,267
Right?

126
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,033
My child...

127
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,833
I don't have to choose.

128
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:02,500
Your father is leaving tomorrow.

129
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,867
You can't guarantee
that they will!

130
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:08,967
The longer they stay here,
the more our family falls apart.

131
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:10,133
Look at what's happening to us!

132
00:06:11,567 --> 00:06:13,300
How can we trust you?

133
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,033
After you betrayed us?

134
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,467
You let him into our house.

135
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:20,367
You're helping him move out.

136
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:22,567
Don't tell me you're
spending money on him, too.

137
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,700
Come on, Mom!

138
00:06:27,067 --> 00:06:29,133
Why? What did that man feed you?

139
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,933
Why are you letting yourself
be fooled by him?

140
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,267
My conscience couldn't take it.

141
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,300
Not helping your father
bothers me.

142
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,700
I can't bear it.

143
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:43,367
Mom, he abandoned us.

144
00:06:44,167 --> 00:06:44,933
Right?

145
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:47,600
His conscience
managed to abandon us.

146
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,100
If he ever has one!
But he doesn't!

147
00:06:51,533 --> 00:06:54,600
And now he has the nerve
to show up in our house,

148
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:56,533
in our lives? For what?
To bring trouble.

149
00:06:56,967 --> 00:06:57,767
Is that it?

150
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:02,667
To put an end to this...

151
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:08,367
Fine, he can stay here
until tomorrow.

152
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:09,933
Max.

153
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:13,167
But if they don't leave
tomorrow...

154
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:15,600
I will.

155
00:07:17,767 --> 00:07:18,600
Andrea.

156
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,033
Andrea!

157
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:26,567
Jeff.

158
00:07:27,967 --> 00:07:29,567
Jeff, Sweetie.

159
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:31,067
Jeff.

160
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,467
Mom.

161
00:07:50,867 --> 00:07:52,200
I'm sorry.

162
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:10,633
Manuel, Jessica, I'm sorry
about what happened.

163
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:13,033
I couldn't stop my children
from acting that way.

164
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:17,233
We should be the ones
apologizing, not you.

165
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:21,067
We brought a lot of
problems into this house.

166
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:25,933
We're very sorry,
Auntie Felma, Coleen.

167
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:27,600
It's not your fault.

168
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:35,733
Let's just focus on how you can
move out for now.

169
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:39,533
I only asked Andrea to let
you stay until tomorrow.

170
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,433
I'll talk to Uncle Abel
first thing in the morning.

171
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:46,867
I'll ask him to come with me
to the landlady he mentioned.

172
00:08:47,467 --> 00:08:51,900
If we're able to pay tomorrow,
we can move in right away.

173
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:54,300
I've already set money aside
for that.

174
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:56,233
But, Felma, that's a loan, okay?

175
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:57,700
We'll pay you back.

176
00:08:58,033 --> 00:09:00,167
The kids might use it against me
later on.

177
00:09:01,933 --> 00:09:03,700
Will I still get to see you?

178
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:09,433
What if your wife finds you...

179
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:11,533
and then takes you away
from us again?

180
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:14,033
Dad, I don't think
I can bear that.

181
00:09:15,233 --> 00:09:17,033
You guys should stay here.

182
00:09:17,167 --> 00:09:19,233
So we can all be together.

183
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:21,667
You'll be safe here.

184
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,167
Don't leave me, Dad.

185
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:28,433
Please stay here.

186
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:33,500
Coleen, that's not possible.

187
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:37,000
Why isn't possible?

188
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:40,967
Because it will hurt Andrea
and Jeffrey's feelings?

189
00:09:42,367 --> 00:09:44,367
Mom, I'm your daughter, too.

190
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:48,900
I have a right
to this house, too.

191
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:53,733
If they can decide,
then so can I.

192
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:59,133
And I decided that dad
and Jessica should stay here.

193
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:02,900
If you're going to kick them
out, then I'm going with them.

194
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,733
We made the right decision,
right?

195
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:15,867
What?

196
00:10:18,533 --> 00:10:20,733
What do you mean? Are you having
second thoughts?

197
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:24,267
Let me remind you...

198
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:26,200
perhaps you've forgotten.

199
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:28,733
We've had several dinners
with nothing to eat.

200
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:32,200
Because mom hasn't been
selling sausages.

201
00:10:33,467 --> 00:10:34,767
<i> No rice?</i>

202
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:37,367
<i> How can I cook rice?</i>

203
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:40,167
<i>Can't you see I'm taking care
of Coleen here?</i>

204
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,567
<i> Why don't you make the rice?</i>

205
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:42,933
<i> There's nothing to cook here.</i>

206
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,867
You even stole fish for us.

207
00:10:47,867 --> 00:10:49,633
<i> Can we have more rice?</i>

208
00:10:49,767 --> 00:10:50,667
<i> Wait a minute.</i>

209
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,367
<i>Miss Cora, just add this
to our debt list.</i>

210
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:55,233
<i>- Thank you!
- This damn kid!</i>

211
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:57,433
And then our neighbors
have done nothing

212
00:10:57,567 --> 00:11:00,533
but gossip about us,
laugh at us.

213
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:03,033
Because that man
has another family.

214
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:05,600
<i>He has another child
in Saudi Arabia.</i>

215
00:11:05,733 --> 00:11:07,000
<i> He got another woman pregnant.</i>

216
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:07,967
<i> That's not true.</i>

217
00:11:08,133 --> 00:11:09,367
<i> Take it back!</i>

218
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,833
<i> Go on! Hit him!</i>

219
00:11:10,967 --> 00:11:12,233
<i> Hit him!</i>

220
00:11:12,367 --> 00:11:13,167
<i> Go on!</i>

221
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,367
<i> You can do it!</i>

222
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,867
<i> Hit him!</i>

223
00:11:16,867 --> 00:11:19,100
Maybe we can ask
Uncle Noah for help.

224
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:19,967
He might be...

225
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:23,467
He might be able to help us
kick that man out.

226
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:32,733
<i>Sorry the subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

227
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:33,500
<i> Please try again later.</i>

228
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:34,933
His phone is off.

229
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:37,600
I'll go to him.

230
00:11:42,133 --> 00:11:44,367
Coleen, you can't go with them.

231
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,633
Why can't I?

232
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:48,267
They're still my family!

233
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:51,600
Sweetie, what about your mom?

234
00:11:51,733 --> 00:11:53,733
She'll miss you.

235
00:11:55,767 --> 00:11:56,467
Sweetie...

236
00:11:59,067 --> 00:12:01,600
Sweetie, you've been
together for so long.

237
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:03,733
She stood as both your father
and mother to you

238
00:12:03,867 --> 00:12:05,367
and your siblings.

239
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,300
And you're going to let
that fall apart just

240
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:10,767
because of me?

241
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:13,100
Sweetie, that's not right, okay?

242
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:15,733
It's not right to hurt them.

243
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:17,567
Especially your mother.

244
00:12:18,533 --> 00:12:22,833
But, Dad, I'm going to miss you.

245
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,233
And Jessica.

246
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:27,800
We'll miss you, too, Coleen.

247
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:30,633
But don't worry,
you can come visit us

248
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:32,800
at our new house, right?

249
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:38,233
How can I even be sure
that I'll see you again?

250
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:44,000
Dad, the last time you left,
I was just a baby.

251
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:47,767
Since then, I'd never
seen you again.

252
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:51,600
Sweetie, sweetie...

253
00:12:51,767 --> 00:12:53,667
I can't make a promise...

254
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:57,133
Because I have no control
over what might happen to me.

255
00:12:59,133 --> 00:12:59,933
Let's just put it
this way, sweetie.

256
00:13:00,067 --> 00:13:02,767
Just remember that we were
together,

257
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:03,867
and we forgave each other.

258
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:07,167
That alone made me very happy.

259
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:10,300
Hush, now.

260
00:13:10,433 --> 00:13:14,333
Don't cry, stop now.

261
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:16,033
Okay?

262
00:13:16,167 --> 00:13:17,967
This is for your own good.

263
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:20,200
So that Hazel won't
bother you anymore.

264
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:23,000
And so that you and
your siblings can make peace.

265
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:25,200
So your family can finally be
at peace.

266
00:13:26,067 --> 00:13:29,600
That's all I want, sweetie.

267
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:33,167
Hush now, stop crying.

268
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,233
Don't cry.

269
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:37,867
Don't cry.

270
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:04,200
I'm sorry.

271
00:14:06,433 --> 00:14:07,767
I don't think it will help you.

272
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:11,833
Felma had made a decision.

273
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,167
I don't think
we can change that.

274
00:14:16,367 --> 00:14:18,167
Is that it, Uncle?

275
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:21,033
You're not going
to fight for her?

276
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:22,267
Even a little?

277
00:14:22,967 --> 00:14:24,333
What for, Dear?

278
00:14:27,067 --> 00:14:28,767
It's hard for me
to fight for her.

279
00:14:32,233 --> 00:14:37,000
Especially now that they're
living under the same roof.

280
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:39,400
But, Uncle, if you show up
at the house,

281
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:41,333
and truly stand by your love
for mom,

282
00:14:42,133 --> 00:14:44,433
it might make him go away.

283
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,233
I have done that.

284
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,900
I tried to stand my ground,
remember?

285
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:52,867
I tried to win her back
many times.

286
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:58,900
But she completely shut me out.

287
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,533
I think it's really over
between us.

288
00:15:03,267 --> 00:15:06,233
But you're still
our father, right?

289
00:15:07,867 --> 00:15:10,100
Can we still come to you?

290
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,367
Your mother has
already cast me aside.

291
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:18,067
Wouldn't it be too much
if I still try to force myself

292
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,500
into your family?

293
00:15:20,133 --> 00:15:22,333
Besides, I'm leaving
for Davao tomorrow.

294
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:25,467
I really need some space
to recover from this.

295
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,567
I think you guys should go.

296
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:34,667
I have an early flight tomorrow.

297
00:15:45,133 --> 00:15:47,467
Jessica, let me do that.

298
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,300
I feel bad to let you do that.

299
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:50,667
It's okay.

300
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:54,400
Dad and I should be the ones
feeling bad for staying here.

301
00:15:54,533 --> 00:15:57,200
Let me help
in my own little way.

302
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:58,700
- As you should!
- To pay for...

303
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:02,000
Because...

304
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:04,100
you can't abuse our kindness.

305
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:07,133
Stop it, Andrea.

306
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:08,067
Why?

307
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:10,433
They're our guests here.

308
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:11,667
Guests?

309
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:18,267
Guests are always welcome
here in our house.

310
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:21,133
She's not welcome here.

311
00:16:21,267 --> 00:16:22,100
Stop it, Andrea.

312
00:16:22,233 --> 00:16:23,200
It's the truth!

313
00:16:24,367 --> 00:16:28,800
Or you can wash the dishes
after you're done cooking.

314
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,367
It's piling up.

315
00:16:32,467 --> 00:16:34,300
Clean the whole kitchen, too.

316
00:16:34,433 --> 00:16:35,500
And the floor.

317
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:37,133
Scrub the tiles clean.

318
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:41,633
Stop.

319
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,267
Here, Didang.

320
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,367
I got this.

321
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,033
Andrea!

322
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:55,767
Sorry.

323
00:16:58,833 --> 00:16:59,767
I mean it!

324
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,633
It's okay, Didang.

325
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:10,200
Andrea, give us
a little more time.

326
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:13,367
Later today or by tomorrow,
we'll be out of here.

327
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:15,233
Well, I can't wait!

328
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:18,700
You're going too far, Andrea!

329
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:20,033
It's okay.

330
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:21,767
Look at you!

331
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,967
Change your clothes.

332
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,467
Hey, what happened?

333
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,367
Why are you crying?

334
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,467
It's nothing, Dad.

335
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:56,900
Is it Andrea?

336
00:17:57,033 --> 00:17:58,433
Did she give you
a hard time again?

337
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:00,467
Dad, I'll be okay.

338
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,167
Don't worry about me.

339
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:08,067
Sweetie, just be patient
with your sister, okay?

340
00:18:08,867 --> 00:18:11,400
Dad, that's what
I've been doing.

341
00:18:12,533 --> 00:18:17,300
It's just sad that she can't
accept me the way Coleen did.

342
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:20,500
Hush...

343
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:22,367
Just endure a little more, okay?

344
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:26,967
Hush, Sweetie, don't cry.

345
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,533
That's enough.

346
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:40,033
Didang, have you brought
Manuel breakfast yet?

347
00:18:40,733 --> 00:18:41,900
- Sweetie, Coleen.
- Mom.

348
00:18:42,033 --> 00:18:45,100
Call your brother and sister now
so we can start eating, okay?

349
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:46,333
- Okay.
- Okay.

350
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,333
Oh, here it is.

351
00:18:51,467 --> 00:18:55,100
I'll just bring food to
Sir Manuel and Jessica, okay?

352
00:18:57,767 --> 00:18:59,600
Good morning, kids.

353
00:18:59,733 --> 00:19:01,533
Come on, Jeffrey. Let's just get
a drive-through.

354
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:03,267
Wait, there's a lot of food
here.

355
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,633
And you're not done with...

356
00:19:04,767 --> 00:19:06,267
I have no appetite, Mom.

357
00:19:07,167 --> 00:19:08,967
I would rather eat out.

358
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:11,067
Where it's peaceful,

359
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:14,467
where I can't hear
someone else's name.

360
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:17,933
Where I can't see
their thick faces.

361
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,367
Andrea, you should
watch your mouth.

362
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:22,433
Your father might hear you.

363
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,100
And so what?

364
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,667
They're the ones who need
a place to stay.

365
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,633
Forcing themselves in here.

366
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:30,367
And we're the ones who
have to adjust for them?

367
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:35,467
Please, just sit down.

368
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:37,033
And then what?

369
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:39,133
We'll all eat together?

370
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,000
Like nothing happened?

371
00:19:42,733 --> 00:19:44,167
When you betrayed us?

372
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:45,500
Andrea, that's enough.

373
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:48,433
Are you getting soft
on them, too, Jeffrey?

374
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:52,433
They don't want us
to eat with them anyway.

375
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:56,567
They want to eat
with those people.

376
00:19:57,867 --> 00:19:59,867
Why don't you call
your dad, Coleen?

377
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,100
You guys can eat together.

378
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,500
You can bond together
for all I care.

379
00:20:05,467 --> 00:20:06,567
Let's go, Jeffrey.

380
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,300
You're not going anywhere!

381
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,167
Don't try my patience, Andrea.

382
00:20:19,033 --> 00:20:20,867
You've been trying my patience.

383
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,700
You're going too far.

384
00:20:23,367 --> 00:20:24,767
You're being disrespectful.

385
00:20:25,467 --> 00:20:27,200
You want things to go your way?

386
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:28,967
You want everyone
to understand you?

387
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:31,733
Does it always have
to be about you?

388
00:20:31,867 --> 00:20:35,067
Well, I'm not letting you
run this house anymore!

389
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,200
I'm the mother here!

390
00:20:36,367 --> 00:20:37,700
And what I say goes!

391
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:39,700
No one leaves this house!

392
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,633
Even Manuel and Jessica.

393
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:43,067
They're not leaving this house!

394
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:53,100
Finally, the truth comes out!

395
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:56,200
You're not kicking those
two out of this house!

396
00:20:56,733 --> 00:20:59,200
You pretend that
they will move out.

397
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:02,233
But the truth is, they will be
staying here!

398
00:21:02,633 --> 00:21:03,700
You know that's not true.

399
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:04,900
You still love him!

400
00:21:05,033 --> 00:21:06,733
That's why you don't
want him to go.

401
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:08,867
Andrea, that's enough.
Stop talking back to her.

402
00:21:09,433 --> 00:21:12,300
That's not the issue here,
you know that.

403
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:15,700
And if I want Manuel
to stay here?

404
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,033
So what?

405
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,833
Who had this house built?

406
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:26,533
Who worked hard to give you
a comfortable life?

407
00:21:27,233 --> 00:21:28,600
Isn't it me?

408
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:30,867
Mom, are you trying
to make us feel bad?

409
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:33,200
We don't talk back, remember?

410
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:34,367
Yes!

411
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,367
Fine!

412
00:21:35,867 --> 00:21:37,833
Let me tell you
everything I've done!

413
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:45,867
To remind you of all the
hardship I've gone through

414
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:49,633
to raise all of you,
so you won't disrespect me!

415
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,800
Just like how this one
is disrespecting me!

416
00:21:52,933 --> 00:21:55,200
I can't be around your ex!

417
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:56,767
Why are you forcing me?

418
00:21:57,233 --> 00:21:58,467
Am I forcing you to?

419
00:21:58,833 --> 00:22:02,833
I just want you
to shut your mouth

420
00:22:02,967 --> 00:22:04,200
if you have nothing nice to say!

421
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:06,167
Instead of making us feel bad!

422
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:08,600
So then it's better
for me to leave!

423
00:22:10,133 --> 00:22:11,567
I said, you're not
going anywhere!

424
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:12,667
I'm an adult now, Mom!

425
00:22:12,933 --> 00:22:14,667
I can take care of myself!

426
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,900
So if you want to take care
of your crippled ex,

427
00:22:18,133 --> 00:22:20,267
then go ahead! Be together!

428
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,000
Mom!

429
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:21,900
Mom, what are you doing?

430
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:23,400
You want to leave?

431
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:25,000
Go ahead! Leave! Go on!

432
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:25,967
- Mom!
- Leave!

433
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:27,433
You want me to walk you outside?

434
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:28,333
Go ahead!

435
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:29,700
Andrea, you have to stop.

436
00:22:30,467 --> 00:22:31,633
<i> You want to leave, right?</i>

437
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,433
<i> Go on! I'll walk you out!</i>

438
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:34,867
<i>Mom, stop it!
Mom, let Andrea go!</i>

439
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:35,733
<i> Get out!</i>

440
00:22:35,867 --> 00:22:36,967
- Let me go!
- Mom!

441
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:37,933
Mom!

442
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:39,300
You're going to
make Andrea leave?

443
00:22:39,433 --> 00:22:40,333
We're going this far?

444
00:22:40,467 --> 00:22:40,967
Yes!

445
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,233
I'm making her leave!

446
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:43,633
That's what she wants, right?

447
00:22:43,767 --> 00:22:44,500
Right?

448
00:22:44,633 --> 00:22:45,800
Felma needs my help.

449
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:47,433
- Didang, help me.
- No, Dad.

450
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:48,767
Dad, you shouldn't
go out there.

451
00:22:48,933 --> 00:22:50,167
But they're fighting.

452
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:52,400
They will get more heated up
if you go out there.

453
00:22:52,533 --> 00:22:53,367
Didang, Didang, please.

454
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:54,767
- Help me.
- Dad, Dad, just stay here.

455
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,700
- Don't go out there.
- My god...

456
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,567
What have I done to my family?

457
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:02,833
Come here!

458
00:23:02,967 --> 00:23:04,300
Mom!

459
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:05,900
What kind of mother are you?

460
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:10,433
Oh, now I'm a bad mother?

461
00:23:11,300 --> 00:23:13,467
Have I done anything wrong?

462
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:18,133
I've been so careful
with everything I do,

463
00:23:18,467 --> 00:23:20,300
just to make things easier
for all of you.

464
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:21,833
And you?

465
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:26,000
Have you ever asked me
how I'm feeling?

466
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:27,400
What I'm thinking?

467
00:23:28,067 --> 00:23:30,300
What I'm going through
with all this?

468
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:32,767
I'm struggling!

469
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:35,200
I'm having such a hard time!

470
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:38,133
Especially when you keep
reminding me

471
00:23:38,267 --> 00:23:40,267
of all your father's mistakes!

472
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,500
<i> I'm hurting!</i>

473
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:44,633
<i> Twice as much!</i>

474
00:23:44,767 --> 00:23:45,833
<i> Twice!</i>

475
00:23:45,967 --> 00:23:47,300
For myself!

476
00:23:48,567 --> 00:23:50,067
And for you!

477
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:56,400
But I choose...

478
00:23:59,167 --> 00:24:01,967
I choose to be a good person.

479
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:05,333
I choose to forgive!

480
00:24:06,333 --> 00:24:08,133
To help!

481
00:24:10,567 --> 00:24:11,300
And you...

482
00:24:11,767 --> 00:24:15,700
Am I forcing you to forgive
your father?

483
00:24:16,367 --> 00:24:19,767
<i>I just didn't want you
to be disrespectful.</i>

484
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:22,700
Don't disrespect me like this!

485
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:26,600
I didn't raise you
to disrespect me like this!

486
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:32,733
For you to talk to me like this
and turn your back on me!

487
00:24:33,233 --> 00:24:38,400
And now you're threatening me
that you'll leave this house?

488
00:24:39,367 --> 00:24:40,100
<i> Go ahead!</i>

489
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:42,433
<i> You can all go!</i>

490
00:24:45,333 --> 00:24:46,267
You can bear that, Mom?

491
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,233
You can live without us?

492
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:52,700
You!

493
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:54,833
And you!

494
00:24:55,833 --> 00:24:59,300
Can you live without me?

495
00:24:59,433 --> 00:25:00,933
Mom, I was just bluffing

496
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:02,667
when I said we're leaving
this house!

497
00:25:03,567 --> 00:25:05,500
But you really
went along with it?

498
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:08,167
Are you that desperate
to be with your ex?

499
00:25:10,033 --> 00:25:16,700
I'm that desperate
to teach you respect!

500
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:25,233
I just want you to respect
my decision as your mom!

501
00:25:28,033 --> 00:25:31,400
I've even compromised, didn't I?

502
00:25:31,533 --> 00:25:32,900
I compromised!

503
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:36,267
But you really don't respect me!

504
00:25:37,233 --> 00:25:41,300
Now, if you don't want to submit
to me as head of this family,

505
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:44,633
if you don't want to obey me...

506
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:48,700
Fine!

507
00:25:49,467 --> 00:25:50,467
Here!

508
00:25:51,867 --> 00:25:53,600
The door is open!

509
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:57,067
Anyone who wants to leave,
go ahead and leave!

510
00:26:01,767 --> 00:26:03,167
Felma, that's enough!

511
00:26:10,533 --> 00:26:13,067
Are you sure that's the
right thing to do, Manuel?

512
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:17,900
If you think this is
the best way to make them learn.

513
00:26:18,033 --> 00:26:19,167
They got me!

514
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:22,467
They realize that Manuel
is in your house.

515
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:23,933
Come on, Paz!

516
00:26:24,067 --> 00:26:25,900
Make sure it's fully charged.

517
00:26:26,033 --> 00:26:27,500
We're going to catch someone.

518
00:26:27,633 --> 00:26:28,900
Call the guard house.

519
00:26:29,033 --> 00:26:33,233
Make sure that Hazel
can't enter this subdivision.

520
00:26:33,367 --> 00:26:36,533
I'm here to pick up a passenger
at Miss Felma Ruiz's house.

521
00:26:36,667 --> 00:26:37,433
Felma!

522
00:26:37,567 --> 00:26:39,200
I know that you're here!
Come out here!

523
